    "A Random Variable (RV) is a variable that probabilistically takes on different values. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Definition\n",
    "\n",
    "The expected value for a discrete random variable is the expected value which is:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$E[X] = \\sum xP(x) $$\n",
    "\n",
    "* X = represents our random variable, can think of it as the set of outcomes, ie the sample space\n",
    "* x = specific value of x "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
